{"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Composing Large Games","generated":true,"anchor":"Composing-Large-Games","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin"]}],"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Content Bundles","modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Give a region its own declarations — its own type, and even its own package.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" shows how a game’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"rules","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" compose from per-region helpers, but its ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"entity declarations"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" all have to stay in the one ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" struct’s body. Content bundles lift that limit. A bundle is a self-contained slice of the world — its own rooms, items, and "},{"code":"@Global","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" state, plus the geography, rules, and verbs that go with them — declared in its own type, and even its own SPM package."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Reach for a bundle when a region is big or independent enough to own its declarations (not just its ","type":"text"},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"code":"rules","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), or when you want to ship a region as a reusable package. For everything smaller, the extension-based file split is lighter and is still the right tool.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"text":"A bundle is a `GameContent`","type":"heading","anchor":"A-bundle-is-a-GameContent"},{"code":["struct Attic: GameContent {","    let landing = Location { name(\"Attic Landing\"); description(\"A dim landing.\") }","    let trunk   = Item { name(\"steamer trunk\"); adjectives(\"steamer\") }","","    var map: WorldMap { trunk.starts(in: landing) }","","    var rules: Rules {","        trunk.before(.open) { try reply(\"It's locked.\") }","    }","","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] {        \/\/ optional — bundles can add verbs too","        SyntaxRule(\"rummage\", slots: .direct, intent: Intent(\"rummage\"))","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"rules","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":" all default to empty, so a bundle declares only what it needs. The bundle stores its declarations exactly as a game does, and the bootstrap discovers them by reflecting over the bundle. Each entity is named after its property, prefixed by the bundle’s "},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"namespace","type":"text"}],"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"namespace","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle"},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trunk"},{"type":"text","text":" → "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"\"Attic.trunk\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"), so a reusable bundle can’t collide with the host."}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"The-game-lists-its-bundles-in-content","text":"The game lists its bundles in `content`","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct MyGame: Game {","    let attic  = Attic()","    let cellar = Cellar()","","    var content: GameContents {","        attic","        cellar","    }","","    var map: WorldMap {","        attic.landing.down(cellar.vault)   \/\/ cross-bundle wiring, top level","        player.starts(in: attic.landing)","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The game’s own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"code":"verbs","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" still work and are merged with every bundle’s."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"The one rule: list the stored instances","anchor":"The-one-rule-list-the-stored-instances","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"content","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must yield the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"same bundle instances the game stores","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"code":"var content { attic; cellar }","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", never "},{"code":"var content { Attic(); Cellar() }","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Each ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" mints a reference token when it’s created, and the bootstrap matches the tokens it discovers against the tokens a bundle’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":" reference. A freshly constructed bundle carries ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"different","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" tokens than the one the game stored, so its references wouldn’t resolve. Listing the stored instances keeps the identities aligned. (The bootstrap reads ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"text":" once and reuses it, so a single build is always self-consistent; the contract matters because the game’s top-level ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":" references the stored ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"attic"},{"text":".)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"EntityIDs are namespaced by the bundle"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A bundle’s entities are namespaced by the bundle, while the game’s own entities stay bare. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"attic.landing"},{"type":"text","text":" becomes "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Attic.landing\""},{"text":"; the game’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"foyer","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" stays ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"foyer\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The namespace defaults to the bundle’s ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"type name"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", so each distinct bundle type gets a distinct prefix automatically and a reusable bundle dropped into any host can’t clash — even if the host and the bundle both declare a ","type":"text"},{"code":"landing","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", they resolve to ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"landing\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"Attic.landing\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". References at the authoring site are token-based (","type":"text"},{"code":"attic.landing","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), so the namespace is invisible there; it only shows up in the raw ID string, which is internal (display and parsing use each entity’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"name(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Collisions are still fatal, but now only when two bundles share a namespace "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"and","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" a property name. That happens when a host stores "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"two instances of the same bundle type"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — both default to the type-name namespace, so "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Attic.landing"},{"type":"text","text":" is declared twice and the bootstrap rejects the game: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"entity \"Attic.landing\" is declared by both Attic and Attic."},{"type":"text","text":" Give each instance a distinct namespace by overriding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"var namespace"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct Attic: GameContent {","    let name: String","    var namespace: String { name }   \/\/ \"NorthAttic\", \"SouthAttic\", …","    \/\/ …","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Because bundle-owned entity IDs are namespaced, so are their save-file keys — a bundle’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Global","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" persists under ","type":"text"},{"code":"Bundle.flag","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Nothing shipped before this change owned bundle content, so there’s no migration; keep a plugin’s own state additive as usual."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Cross-bundle references","anchor":"Cross-bundle-references","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Top-level wiring"}]},{"text":" — a game connecting one bundle’s room to another’s — is ordinary, compile-checked property access: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"attic.landing.down(cellar.vault)"},{"text":". Renaming either room breaks the exit at compile time.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Bundle-to-bundle","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" references (a bundle that needs to point at another bundle’s entity from ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"inside"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" its own ","type":"text"},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"code":"rules","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") use explicit injection: construct the dependency first and hand the shared instance in (","type":"text"},{"code":"Attic(cellarDoor: cellar.door)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), so both sides reference the same token. Keep these localized; most cross-region wiring belongs at the top level.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","text":"Multi-package","anchor":"Multi-package","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because a bundle is a self-contained "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" value type, it can live in its own SPM module: export the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent"},{"type":"text","text":" type, depend on it from the host, and list it in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"type":"text","text":". Nothing else changes."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Worked example","anchor":"Worked-example","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tests\/GnustoTests\/Support\/BundleGame\/"},{"text":" is a minimal game built this way: ","type":"text"},{"code":"AtticContent","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"CellarContent","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" each own a room, an item, and rules (the attic also adds a ","type":"text"},{"code":"rummage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" verb), and ","type":"text"},{"code":"BundleGame","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" composes them with a cross-bundle exit. ","type":"text"},{"code":"BundleCompositionTests","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" boots it and confirms every bundle’s rules and verbs fire, the cross-bundle exit traverses both ways, each bundle’s IDs are namespaced by its type, and two instances sharing a namespace are rejected.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For a bundle that also carries logic over the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"host’s","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" world — a content-bearing plugin — see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/contentbundles"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GamePlugin":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}],"role":"symbol","title":"GamePlugin","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gameplugin","abstract":[{"text":"A reusable game system — commerce, combat, dialog, magic — packaged as an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"importable unit of ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"verbs"}]},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"rules"}]},{"type":"text","text":", that a host game opts into."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContents":{"fragments":[{"tex